com.ibm.team.repository.client

Interface IUploadHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    UploadAdapter

    public interface IUploadHandler
    Accepts events regarding a upload being managed by a IContentManagerSession and provides data needed to upload content.
    Since:
    0.6

      • uploadFailed

        boolean uploadFailed(TeamRepositoryException e,
                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
        Called when the upload fails. If this method returns true, the failure will be silently ignored and the upload will be retried with new parameters obtained from the receiver.
        Parameters:
        e - The failure. May have wrapped exceptions.
        Returns:
        true if the caller should retry, false otherwise
        Since:
        0.7
